Register the new plugin in the build system and provide a KDL layout snippet.

Build integration:
- Add `"default-plugins/tequila-review-mode"` to workspace members in root `Cargo.toml`
- Add a `WorkspaceMember` entry in `xtask/src/main.rs` `workspace_members()` function

KDL layout:
- Create `.tequila/tasks/0003-add-review-mode/review-layout.kdl` as a reference layout snippet showing how to launch the plugin as a pinned floating pane:
  - Positioned at top: `y 0`
  - Height ~75%: `height "75%"`
  - Full width: `width "100%"`
  - This leaves the bottom ~25% visible for the Claude command line

Keybinding:
- Add a `tequila-review-mode` plugin alias in the `plugins` section of `~/.config/zellij/config.kdl`
- Bind `Alt+V` in `shared_except "locked"` to `LaunchOrFocusPlugin "tequila-review-mode"` with `floating true`

Verify the plugin compiles with `cargo xtask build`.